  serue a good Master, is verie happie; for such a Master serues in stead of a
  Father, a Councellor, a Tutor. And this was this seruants happinesse, to haue
  so good a Master as this Centurion, heere spoken of, who saith, Puer meus
  jacet, &amp;c.
               
               
