children, his houses, his flocks, and his substance, as he did when his wife
said vnto him, Curse God and die; but that was as a dagger to his
heart. Shall I be angrie and offended with my God? No, though he should kill
mee, yet will I loue him: For I haue no other Good but my God, he is all my
hope, and all my comfort. What then might our Sauiour thinke of the Deuil? How
much should it grieue him to heare him say, Fal down and worship
me.
            
