  embleme of weakenesse) hath her greatest force and strength in her tongue:
  Your Ruffians, and such as are swaggering fellows, haue more tongue than hands;
  but they that are truly valiant, haue more hand than tongue, they know not what
  the tongue meanes. The Roman Souldiers drew a Hand for their Deuice. In the
