  against Vertue, with Vertue; against Fasting, with Fasting; against Prayer,
  with Prayer; against Mercie, with Mercie; and against Miracles, by crauing
  other Miracles. And if it were abhominable before God, that a man should put on
  womans apparell, and a woman, mans, (as it is in Deutronomie) much
  worse will it seem in his sight, that the euill man should put on the disguise
  of him that is good, &amp; that Vice should put on Vertue's cloathes. In
  Ecclesiasticus God threatneth the Hypocrites,
