  in homine est Regina potentiarum h
                        •
                     manarum, Mans Will is the Queene of humane faculties: To whose
  charge is committed the treating and obtaining of our desired ends; and is so
  absolute a Soueraigne, that although the Vnderstanding be in it selfe so noble,
