  Empresse, against whom none ought to display their Banner; she finds her selfe
  especially offended, and counts it a kind of high treason, that humane Will
  should rebel against her, there being no other Wil neither in heauen, nor in
  earth, more than the Wil of God: And this Lesson we are taught in our Pater
  noster, Thy Kingdome come; thy Will be done in earth, as it is in heauen.
  The earth is thy Kingdome, as well as the heauen; and therefore, thy Will be
  done in earth, as it is in heauen. Now the Scribes and Pharisees growing into
