  our children wee make little reckoning, but of the wealth that we are to leaue
  them, exceeding much: Being like vnto that sicke man, who not thinking of the
  danger wherein he is, cuts him out new cloathes, and entertaineth new
  seruants. A Gentleman will take more care of his Horse, and a great Lord of his
  estate, than of his children: For his Horse, the one will looke out a good
  rider, and such a one as shal see him well fed and drest; The other, a very
