  had he done well, hee should not (considerng there was warre betweene them)
  haue gone disarmed. What saith Saint Paul vnto thee, Accipite
  Armaturam Fidei. Those weapons of Faith,
                     Ephes.
 6. together with it's Armour, are of more inchantment against Hell,
  than those which the Fables feigne to be wrought by Vulcan. That which
  imports a Christian, is neuer to goe without them, because he is in a
  continuall warfare.
