               This Ibat doth inforce a perseuerance and continuation,
  in token that God wil leaue his best beloued countrie, &amp; that citie which
  was most graced and fauored by him, if it be so gracelesse as to prooue
  vngratefull. When God carried Ezechiel in spirit to the Temple,
  discouering great abhominations vnto him, and said vnto him, These things my
  People commit, Vt procul recedam à Sanctuario meo, They giue
  mee occasion thereby to forsake them, and to get mee farre enough from them. So
