  and of ioy, though in a different manner do dayly cause the like. For this our
  not eating nor drinking occasioned by passion, doth debilitate our forces, and
  weakens our strength; but beeing assisted by the helpe of the holy Spirit, it
  doth not onely conserue, but renew our strength, and put as it were new mettle
  into vs; as was to be seene in Elias, who with that water and bread
  which the Angell gaue him, went vp to Mount Horeb, &amp; there fasted 40 days.
