sprouting forth of it, sicut nouellae Oliuarum. The Cypresse is the
Symbole of beautie; for although it beareth no fruit, yet it shoots vp like a
Pyramis, to an extraordinarie heigth: and both of them make the stampe
of a holy Prelate, whose mercie and compassion is most fruitfull, and whose
prayer is most beautifull and pleasing: for there is not any thing that man
can imagine to bee more faire, than that a creature by this meanes should come
to grow so sweetly familiar with his Creator.
            
               
