  thoughts from the vertue of those diuine hands. And therefore it was fit &amp;
  conuenient, that he should adde an augmentation vnto them, but not create
  them: as at the wedding he turned the water into wine, which he could (if he
  would) haue created anew. Saint Augustine saith, That this
