haue their eyes full of Adulteries. Plutarch reporteth, That a
certaine Conquerour entring the Citie in triumph, casting his eye aside vpon a
handsome young woman, had his heart taken prisoner by her; and sending his
lookes still after her, he gaue occasion to Diogenes to breake this
jeast vpon him, That this faire mayden had like a Chicken wrung his necke thus
aside, looking still backward as his Chariot went forward.
            
