relieuing (being importuned therunto) two of his brethren with 200 Crownes, for
to buy them Oxen to till their ground. I shall (said he) desire of God, That
this poore pittance which I now giue you, doe not consume the rest of that
which ye now enioy. My brethren, to facilitate their request, told me that I
was a single man, had no body to care for,Kindred will
  cleaue to a man in his prosperity, but neuer look on him in aduersitie.
