               If thou be the Christ, tell vs plainly. In three words
they vttered three notorious lies:The subteltie of the
  Iewes in circumuenting our Sauiour.
            
            The first, Dic nobis palam, Tell vs plainly; for all that
thou hast hitherto sayd vnto vs, is as nothing.
            The second, Dic nobis palam, and we will beleeue
thee.
            The third, Dic nobis palam; for that is the reason why
wee haue not hitherto beleeued thee. Saint Augustine and Saint
Chrysostome haue both obserued, that in these their lies there was a
great deale of craft &amp; subtletie; which was this, That the Iewes did still
