then, God being willing to giue vs a taste of them; for the Soule that once
tasteth of the sweetnesse of teares, will not leaue them for a world: for, as
those vapors that are exhaled from those salt and bitter waters of the sea,
being conuerted into clouds, are afterwards resolued into a sweet and sauorie
water; so those sighes and sobbs arising from a sad and sorrowfull Soule for
hauing offended the Maiestie of God, beeing conuerted into Clouds of feare,
resolue themselues at last into most sweet &amp; most sauorie teares.Teares sometimes denied vs for our punishment.
