not incline to a lye. Aeneas Syluius reporteth, That
Fredericke Archduke of Austria, would goe a nights disguised through
the Tauerns and Victualing houses belonging to the Court, only to heare what
they sayd of himselfe, and his Ministers; &amp; being demanded, why he did
expose his person to that perill? his answer was, Because in Court they neuer
tell truth. Plutarch recounteth of King Antiochus, That
hauing lost himselfe a hunting, hee lighted vpon a Cottage where were a
