the King and his Ministers? The King (said they) hath the report of a good
honest gentleman, but that the State was neuer worse gouerned than now, for it
is serued by the greediest and the gripingest Ministers that were in the
world: and when he came backe againe to Court, he told those that were about
him; Since I first tooke possession of this my Kingdome, I neuer heard the
truth of things till yesterday. Amongst foure hundred Prophets, which
Ahab consulted,3. Reg. 22. onely
hee met with one that would not lye vnto him, and the King hated him for
telling him the truth. Saint Ambrose calls the Pallace,
Basilica, deriuing it from the Basiliske, which kills with it's looke.
