            But some one will aske me, How comes it to passe, that this Theefe
in so short a space knew the set time and season of this his happy chance, when
as Ierusalem in so many yeares could not light vpon the like encounter? S.
Augustine, S. Chrysostome, and Leo, answer
hereunto; That he had Christ for his Master, who reuealed the same vnto him,
complying with that deliuered by Ieremie, De coelo misit ignem, &amp; eru
diuit me. Gregorie Nissen saith, Repleuit eum eruditione Spiritus
Sancti. Cromatius; In ipso crucis candelabro sol resplenduit, The Sun did shine
vnto him vpon the candlesticke of the Crosse. Theophilact doth here apply
